Firstly Download Apache2 Web server in RPI-3:
Type below commands in terminal.
 sudo apt-get update
 sudo apt-get upgrade
 sudo apt-get install apache2

Secondly, Next Steps are : 
Type below commands in terminal.
 sudo chmod 777   /var/www/html  # Change mode
 sudo chown -R pi /var/www       # Change owner
 mkdir /var/www/html/cgi-bin     # make directory cgi-bin            
 cd cgi-bin                      # change directory to cgi-bin
 
 Thirdly,
 create test.py cgi file in this directory and write cgi code.
 
 Hence forth ,
 In Terminal Type :
            1.sudo a2enmod cgi 
            2.sudo service apache2 restart
 
 To test CGI CODE :
 In WebBrowser Type  http://YOUR_LOCAL_IP_OF_RPI3/cgi-bin/test.py
 
